<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (for whom these are) well developed</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (he is free of grief and) his rebirths have come to an end [TB] he is free of grief (and his rebirths have come to an end)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] [he who] (has perfect understanding and) is not attached to rebirth [TB] [he who] has perfect understanding and is not (attached to rebirth)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] For [a monk] who is proud (and negligent)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (virtue, meditation) and wisdom</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] it rains down on something that is covered</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (so) it does not rain down on it [TB] so (it does not rain down on it)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (the wise man) [should] always [train on] in virtues</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>151-152</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:chakravarti1930"/><citedRange>69-71</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.6.11b <hi>yasya hy ete subhāvitāḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">This seems to be the end of Uv. 6.11b, though in Bernhard’s edition it reads <hi>subhāvitāḥ</hi> and has no other variant reading than <hi>subhāvitā</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.6.11d <hi>tv aśokaḥ kṣīṇasaṃbhavaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.6.12b <hi>ājñātāvī niraupadhiḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment">Uv.6.13a <hi>uddhatasya pramattasya</hi></note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">Uv.6.13c <hi>śīlaṃ samādhiḥ prajñā ca</hi></note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.6.14a <hi>channam evābhivarṣati</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.6.14d <hi>evaṃ taṃ nābhivarṣati</hi></note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.6.15b <hi>sadā śīleṣu paṇḍitaḥ</hi></note></p>
         </div>
